	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />For older homebrew stuff (and newer) <a href="http://nesworld.com/homebrew.php" class="postlink">NESWorld</a> has a nice layout and a very comprehensive library.  I'm sure once the entries for this contest are posted, they will end up on that site as well.  
<br />
<br />As for utilities/tools/editors, there are so many out there it would be a PITA to keep the updated versions on the site.  I don't want to lose the simplicity of the site, but will definitely add a "Interested in more Homebrew?" page with plenty of links to other sources.
<br />
<br />As for the nesdev homepage, I never look at it.  Since the info was added to the wiki, I see no need for it.

		

		</td>
