	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Denine wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Maaan,I alwazs wanted to compete in compo.<br />From what I understand:<br />1.It already started(January 1st)<br />2.Everyone can enter at any time,except deadline(June 1st)<br />3.It can be any mapper,OR NROM(Depend what category you're in)<br />No for questions:<br />1.Is there any sign in deadline?<br />2.If I sign my game in compo,can I later use it in different project?<br />I mean,not in another compo.But I want  to make Dizzy Rainy Day+that game(2 game on 1 cart).Is this ok?<br />3.Is it ok to post ANY kind of game,even with minimalistic grafics?<br /><br />Sorry,I know some questions sounds dumb <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>
<br />There are no dumb questions <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />
<br />
<br />You don't have to officially "sign up" for anything.  Whatever comes in before the deadline qualifies.  Submit whatever you like, in whatever state you wish.  If there is only one submission in that category you could win.  Obviously the better it is, the better chance of winning you will have.  Hopefully there will be enough entries that we won't have to award a prize to something whipped up in 20 minutes.
<br />
<br />It's your game, you can do what you want with it.  This is a fun competition, not a legal obligation.  The only thing to keep in mind, is if you plan on making it a RetroUSB release, it might hurt your sales if someone can freely download the rom.  I guess we can remove it from the site by request, but the idea is to have a place to download these games.  If everyone wanted their roms private, then it would kind of ruin the spirit of the whole thing.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
